        "content": "\n**`countSelected`**\n```go\nfunc TestCountSelected(t *testing.T) {\n\tcases := []struct {\n\t\tname     string\n\t\tselected map[int]bool\n\t\twant     int\n\t}{\n\t\t{\"empty\", map[int]bool{}, 0},\n\t\t{\"none true\", map[int]bool{0: false, 1: false}, 0},\n\t\t{\"some true\", map[int]bool{0: true, 1: false, 2: true}, 2},\n\t\t{\"all true\", map[int]bool{0: true, 1: true}, 2},\n\t}\n\tfor _, c := range cases {\n\t\tt.Run(c.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\t\tm := &model{selected: c.selected}\n\t\t\tif got := m.countSelected(); got != c.want {\n\t\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"got %d, want %d\", got, c.want)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t})\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n**`articlesSaved`**\n```go\nfunc TestArticlesSaved(t *testing.T) {\n\tcases := []struct {\n\t\tname  string\n\t\tlines []string\n\t\twant  int\n\t}{\n\t\t{\"empty\", nil, 0},\n\t\t{\"no matches\", []string{\"info: starting\", \"done\"}, 0},\n\t\t{\"some matches\", []string{\"  - 'title one' (2026-01-01)\", \"info\", \"  - 'title two' (2026-01-02)\"}, 2},\n\t\t{\"prefix must be exact\", []string{\"- 'not indented'\"}, 0}, // documents the strict \"  - \" prefix requirement\n\t}\n\tfor _, c := range cases {\n\t\tt.Run(c.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\t\tif got := articlesSaved(c.lines); got != c.want {\n\t\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"got %d, want %d\", got, c.want)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t})\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n**`truncate`** — this one has a real latent bug worth a dedicated test:\n```go\nfunc TestTruncate(t *testing.T) {\n\tcases := []struct {\n\t\tname string\n\t\ts    string\n\t\tn    int\n\t\twant string\n\t}{\n\t\t{\"shorter than limit\", \"abc\", 10, \"abc\"},\n\t\t{\"exact length\", \"abcde\", 5, \"abcde\"},\n\t\t{\"needs truncation\", \"abcdefgh\", 5, \"abcd…\"},\n\t\t{\"n<=1 returns raw slice, no ellipsis\", \"abcdef\", 1, \"a\"},\n\t\t{\"n<=0 edge case\", \"abcdef\", 0, \"\"},\n\t}\n\tfor _, c := range cases {\n\t\tt.Run(c.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\t\tif got := truncate(c.s, c.n); got != c.want {\n\t\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"got %q, want %q\", got, c.want)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t})\n\t}\n}\n\n// Gap: truncate() uses len(s)/s[:n] on BYTES, not runes. Any provider or\n// log-line text containing multi-byte UTF-8 (accented French/Malagasy\n// characters are plausible in this domain, e.g. \"Madagascar-Tribuné\")\n// can be sliced mid-rune, producing mangled output in viewRunning's\n// %-18s padding. Add once a real multi-byte input is confirmed in scope:\nfunc TestTruncate_MultibyteSafety(t *testing.T) {\n\ts := \"café-madagascar\" // é is 2 bytes in UTF-8\n\tgot := truncate(s, 5)\n\tif !utf8ValidTail(got) {\n\t\tt.Errorf(\"truncate produced invalid UTF-8 by cutting mid-rune: %q\", got)\n\t}\n}\n```\n*(`utf8ValidTail` would just wrap `utf8.ValidString`; flagging this as a genuine correctness gap, not just a missing test — worth a `utf8.RuneCountInString`-based rewrite if non-ASCII names are ever expected.)*\n\n**`layout`**\n```go\nfunc TestLayout_ClampsToMinimums(t *testing.T) {\n\tm := &model{width: 5, height: 2} // smaller than borders/margins\n\tw, h := m.layout()\n\tif w < 10 {\n\t\tt.Errorf(\"width not clamped: got %d, want >= 10\", w)\n\t}\n\tif h < 3 {\n\t\tt.Errorf(\"height not clamped: got %d, want >= 3\", h)\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc TestLayout_NormalSize(t *testing.T) {\n\tm := &model{width: 100, height: 40}\n\tw, h := m.layout()\n\tif want := 100 - sidenavWidth - 4; w != want {\n\t\tt.Errorf(\"width: got %d, want %d\", w, want)\n\t}\n\tif want := 40 - 6; h != want {\n\t\tt.Errorf(\"height: got %d, want %d\", h, want)\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n**`highlighted`**\n```go\nfunc TestHighlighted(t *testing.T) {\n\tm := &model{runOrder: []string{\"a\", \"b\", \"c\"}}\n\tcases := []struct{ cursor, want int }{}\n\t_ = cases\n\tm.runCursor = -1\n\tif got := m.highlighted(); got != \"\" {\n\t\tt.Errorf(\"negative cursor: got %q, want empty\", got)\n\t}\n\tm.runCursor = 3\n\tif got := m.highlighted(); got != \"\" {\n\t\tt.Errorf(\"out-of-range cursor: got %q, want empty\", got)\n\t}\n\tm.runCursor = 1\n\tif got := m.highlighted(); got != \"b\" {\n\t\tt.Errorf(\"valid cursor: got %q, want b\", got)\n\t}\n\tm2 := &model{runOrder: nil, runCursor: 0}\n\tif got := m2.highlighted(); got != \"\" {\n\t\tt.Errorf(\"empty runOrder: got %q, want empty\", got)\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n",
        "level": 3
      },
      {
        "title": "State-machine functions — currently untested, moderate effort",
        "content": "\n**`handleKey`** — the biggest gap. Every screen/key combination is a branch with no coverage:\n\n```go\nfunc newTestModel() *model {\n\tm := newModel(10, \"../crawler\")\n\treturn m\n}\n\nfunc TestHandleKey_Picking_CursorBounds(t *testing.T) {\n\tm := newTestModel()\n\tm.handleKey(teaKeyMsg(\"up\")) // already at 0, should not go negative\n\tif m.cursor != 0 {\n\t\tt.Errorf(\"cursor went negative: %d\", m.cursor)\n\t}\n\tm.cursor = len(providers) - 1\n\tm.handleKey(teaKeyMsg(\"down\"))\n\tif m.cursor != len(providers)-1 {\n\t\tt.Errorf(\"cursor exceeded bounds: %d\", m.cursor)\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc TestHandleKey_Picking_ToggleAndSelectAll(t *testing.T) {\n\tm := newTestModel()\n\tm.handleKey(teaKeyMsg(\" \"))\n\tif !m.selected[0] {\n\t\tt.Fatal(\"space did not toggle selection\")\n\t}\n\tm.handleKey(teaKeyMsg(\"a\"))\n\tif m.countSelected() != len(providers) {\n\t\tt.Fatal(\"'a' did not select all providers\")\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc TestHandleKey_Picking_EnterWithNoneSelectedSelectsAll(t *testing.T) {\n\tm := newTestModel()\n\tm.handleKey(teaKeyMsg(\"enter\"))\n\tif m.countSelected() != len(providers) {\n\t\tt.Error(\"enter with 0 selected should default to all\")\n\t}\n\tif m.screen != screenLimit {\n\t\tt.Error(\"enter should advance to screenLimit\")\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc TestHandleKey_Limit_InvalidInputIgnored(t *testing.T) {\n\tm := newTestModel()\n\tm.screen = screenLimit\n\tm.limitInput.SetValue(\"-5\")\n\tm.handleKey(teaKeyMsg(\"enter\"))\n\tif m.screen != screenLimit {\n\t\tt.Error(\"negative limit should not advance screen\")\n\t}\n\tm.limitInput.SetValue(\"not-a-number\")\n\tm.handleKey(teaKeyMsg(\"enter\"))\n\tif m.screen != screenLimit {\n\t\tt.Error(\"non-numeric limit should not advance screen\")\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc TestHandleKey_Limit_ZeroIsValid(t *testing.T) {\n\t// 0 means \"unlimited\" per the flag docstring in main.go — make sure\n\t// handleKey doesn't reject it (only \"< 0\" is rejected).\n\tt.Skip(\"startRun() spawns goroutines against m.program which is nil in tests — needs seam\")\n}\n\nfunc TestHandleKey_Running_QuitBlockedWhilePending(t *testing.T) {\n\tm := newTestModel()\n\tm.screen = screenRunning\n\tm.pending = 2\n\t_, cmd := m.handleKey(teaKeyMsg(\"q\"))\n\tif cmd != nil {\n\t\tt.Error(\"q should be a no-op while providers are still running\")\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc TestHandleKey_Running_QuitAllowedWhenDone(t *testing.T) {\n\tm := newTestModel()\n\tm.screen = screenRunning\n\tm.pending = 0\n\t_, cmd := m.handleKey(teaKeyMsg(\"q\"))\n\tif cmd == nil {\n\t\tt.Error(\"q should quit once all providers are done\")\n\t}\n}\n\n// teaKeyMsg is a small helper mapping key strings to tea.KeyMsg — bubbletea\n// doesn't expose a public constructor from string, so build via known Type\n// constants (tea.KeyUp, tea.KeySpace, tea.KeyEnter, tea.KeyRunes{...}, etc.)\n```\n\n**`Update`** — message dispatch, currently untested:\n```go\nfunc TestUpdate_StatusMsgAppendsLineAndRefreshesOnlyWhenHighlighted(t *testing.T) {\n\tm := newTestModel()\n\tm.runOrder = []string{\"provider-a\", \"provider-b\"}\n\tm.runCursor = 0\n\tm.statuses[\"provider-a\"] = &providerStatus{}\n\tm.statuses[\"provider-b\"] = &providerStatus{}\n\n\tm.Update(statusMsg{provider: \"provider-b\", line: \"hello\"})\n\tif len(m.statuses[\"provider-b\"].lines) != 1 {\n\t\tt.Fatal(\"line not appended for non-highlighted provider\")\n\t}\n\tif m.vp.View() != \"\" && strings.Contains(m.vp.View(), \"hello\") {\n\t\tt.Error(\"viewport should not refresh for a non-highlighted provider\")\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc TestUpdate_DoneMsg_ErrorPathSetsErrorStateAndAppendsMessage(t *testing.T) {\n\tm := newTestModel()\n\tm.pending = 1\n\tm.statuses[\"p\"] = &providerStatus{state: stateRunning}\n\tm.Update(doneMsg{provider: \"p\", err: errors.New(\"boom\")})\n\tst := m.statuses[\"p\"]\n\tif st.state != stateError {\n\t\tt.Error(\"expected stateError\")\n\t}\n\tif m.pending != 0 {\n\t\tt.Error(\"pending should decrement on done, error or not\")\n\t}\n\tif !strings.Contains(st.lines[len(st.lines)-1], \"boom\") {\n\t\tt.Error(\"error message not appended to lines\")\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc TestUpdate_DoneMsg_SuccessPath(t *testing.T) {\n\tm := newTestModel()\n\tm.pending = 1\n\tm.statuses[\"p\"] = &providerStatus{state: stateRunning}\n\tm.Update(doneMsg{provider: \"p\", err: nil})\n\tif m.statuses[\"p\"].state != stateDone {\n\t\tt.Error(\"expected stateDone\")\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc TestUpdate_WindowSizeMsg_RecomputesLayoutAndViewport(t *testing.T) {\n\tm := newTestModel()\n\tm.Update(tea.WindowSizeMsg{Width: 100, Height: 40})\n\tif m.width != 100 || m.height != 40 {\n\t\tt.Error(\"dimensions not stored\")\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n**`startRun`** — currently untestable as written (nil `m.program` panic in the goroutine on first `Send`). This is the most important structural gap:\n```go\nfunc TestStartRun_BuildsRunOrderFromSelection(t *testing.T) {\n\tt.Skip(`startRun spawns goroutines that call m.program.Send() unconditionally.\n\tRecommended seam: extract the \"build runOrder + statuses\" bookkeeping into\n\ta pure helper (e.g. m.prepareRun()) that startRun calls before spawning\n\tgoroutines, so runOrder/statuses/pending can be asserted without needing\n\ta live tea.Program or real subprocess.`)\n}\n```\n\n",
        "level": 3
      },
      {
        "title": "Integration-level gaps (no coverage of any kind today)",
        "content": "\n1. **End-to-end headless run** — spin up `runHeadless` against a fake `crawlerDir` containing a stub `main.py` (shell script or trivial Python) that echoes deterministic lines and exits 0/1, asserting stdout output format `\"[%s] %s\\n\"` and error formatting.\n2. **TUI full lifecycle** — using `teatest` (bubbletea's testing helper package) to drive `newModel` through picking → limit → running screens and assert final rendered output, exercising `Update`/`View` together rather than in isolation.\n3. **Crawler-dir misconfiguration** — `--crawler-dir` pointing at a nonexistent path; currently the failure surfaces only as an opaque `exec` error with no user-facing hint about which flag caused it.\n4. **Signal handling / partial completion** — quitting (`q`) is blocked while `pending > 0` in the running screen, but there's no test (and no cleanup code) for what happens to in-flight `exec.Cmd` subprocesses if the *program itself* is killed externally (e.g. ctrl+c at the OS level bypassing the TUI's own quit gate) — orphaned `uv run main.py` processes are a plausible real-world gap.\n\n---\n\n",
        "level": 3
      },
      {
        "title": "Priority order if implementing",
        "content": "1. Pure functions (`truncate`, `articlesSaved`, `countSelected`, `layout`, `highlighted`) — zero refactor needed, highest ROI.\n2. `handleKey` / `Update` via constructed `model` structs and synthetic messages — no refactor needed.\n3. Add the `startRun`/`runCrawler` injection seams (function-typed fields for the command runner and for `program.Send`), then cover concurrency and subprocess-error paths.\n4. `teatest`-based integration test for the full picking→limit→running flow.",
        "level": 3
      }
    ],
